parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the body control module can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Turn signals not working
repeated replacement of the body control module.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress and Electrical Component Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress can cause electrical component failure, leading to safety risks, including burning odors and damage to the vehicle's interior.
symptoms: Water leaking into the interior
water damage to floorboards
burning odor in the interior
electrical component failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can increase the risk of accidents, especially when reversing, and can cause inconvenience to drivers who rely on this feature.
symptoms: Intermittent non-functional backup camera
red triangle and red camera icon on the screen
connection concerns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel gauge can cause inconvenience and safety risks, as drivers may not be aware of the actual fuel level, leading to potential running out of fuel.
symptoms: Intermittent failure of the fuel gauge to show the correct fuel level
fuel gauge resetting when the car is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical and electronic malfunctions can cause various safety risks, including malfunctioning of critical systems, and can lead to inconvenience and frustration.
symptoms: Intermittent malfunctioning of various electrical systems
including the HD surround vision camera recorder
dashboard displays
and electronic components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the rearview camera can increase the risk of accidents, especially when reversing, as the driver may not have a clear view of the surrounding area.
symptoms: The rearview camera screen goes blank
displays a black screen with a red circle and slash
or a red triangle with an exclamation mark
and may work only 50% of the time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended activation of the Automatic Emergency Braking system can cause unexpected and abrupt stops, which can lead to accidents, especially when reversing down a slope.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly and strongly brakes without warning
often accompanied by a loud noise
and may occur when reversing down a slope.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the auto-stop feature can cause the vehicle to shut down unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded in traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down unexpectedly
the "stability track off" message appears on the dashboard
the auto-stop feature turns off and on repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent transmission shifting problems can cause the vehicle to stutter or hesitate when shifting gears, potentially leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The transmission shifts erratically
the vehicle stutters or hesitates when shifting gears
the problem occurs intermittently with no clear starting point.
